    "summary": "I am Wesley. Expert in persuasive design. I help you create solutions that solve the right problems. To discover the behavioural patterns that make or break your service. The patterns you need to influence to be successful. \n\nUnderstand the problem before committing to a solution. With analytical and creative thinking, I challenge you to look at your challenges from the perspective of your user. To understand why they behave as they do. And to create new concepts that will inspire (new) behaviour and improve your service. \n\nWith an applicable model we\u2019ll squeeze all the value that behavioural psychology and gamification has to offer to transform your service into a persuasive experience that people will love. \n\nI\u2019ve been able to do so for clients like ING Bank, EY, Zwijssen and UMCU as well as award-winning start-ups like SafeDrivePod and Mobietrain.\n\nI desire to inspire, not just influence. To persuade and not coerce. To motivate, not force. Persuasive design allows me to speak to people\u2019s intrinsic desire and purpose with concepts and solutions. To empower people to engage in and enjoy what they do. To grow and succeed. For learners, employees or clients. From apps to workshops, onboarding, learning experiences or articles. I can help you build a better experience.",
